		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well it's easier to have your files in the same directory, but probably a better idea would be to have them in different ones like you said. But you don't NEED to incbin any files if you don't want. You can do db statements to define every byte in your code. Why you would want to define every byte instead of incbining a CHR file, I don't know. But you'll probably want to be incbining alot as you progress in your code. And also, one picky lame thing I'd like to just mention, please don't double-post. Copy the text from the old post into notepad, delete the old post, make a new post, paste the text from the old post into the new post, and continue off of that one. Okay? Sorry, just takes up thread space, and is kind of annoying.

		

